GNU *Zile* ("Zile Implements Lua Editors") "is a text editor development kit, so that you can (relatively) quickly develop your own ideal text editor without reinventing the wheel for many of the common algorithms and data-structures needed to do so."

Prior to version 3 it was GNU *Zile* ("Zile Is Lossy Emacs") is a lightweight ErsatzEmacs from the Free Software Foundation. It attempts to emulate the behavior of its "big brother" in a small package, so that Emacs users can feel at home in limited environments.

For customization, Zile uses its own limited configuration language known as *Zile Lisp*.
Zile Lisp is a tiny subset of Emacs Lisp that consists of the Zile commands plus `setq'.

* http://www.gnu.org/software/zile/

